			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>They drop off trash mobs in Ferubi, a zone off of Qinimi which anyone can reach from Natimbi.  I think the level 55 or 60 level req is all.  Be advised, trash mobs in Ferubi can hit for over 1K though they do that a lot less since the retune.  Ferubi is an indoor zone with trash mobs running at near-SOW speeds.  I have run speed 4 and the nocs can catch me from behind on pulls.  Besides the static spawns on the walkways, there are random Ukun hound type mobs that spawn and cast a wicked snare called Ukun Chains.  If you're out pulling for your group and an Ukun lands this snare on you, you will more than likely die.
<br />

<br />
And the last reason I would go flocking to Ferubi to look for those shoulders is that they are insanely rare.  I have easily killed 1000 or more mobs there with my groups and small raids and never seen them.
<br />

<br />
But we can always hope.</span></td>
