				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: new shoulders...<a name="44262"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Jun 4 04 4:42 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span><blockquote><b>Quote:</b><br><span class="quote">Be advised, trash mobs in Ferubi can hit for over 1K though they do that a lot less since the retune. Ferubi is an indoor zone with trash mobs running at near-SOW speeds. I have run speed 4 and the nocs can catch me from behind on pulls.</span></blockquote>
<br />

<br />
Been about 20 hours in there (just for loot and exp). 2 of the 25/25/25 augments (lost both rolls) and these shoulders. Steppy is DEAD on with what he said. Trash hits for 800, there are a few AoE DD and Dots, and there is also the occational mob (the dudes with the chains hanging off the necks) that hit for 1100 a pop (add in rampage and flurry on some too). Bottom line, this is <b>not</b> a pickup group zone.
<br />

<br />
As far as run speed the dogs are the fastest, with Run speed 4 they catch me and they hit really hard from behind. It is not an easy zone, if you wipe it can be a hard CR, really hard if you have no summoning ability (or item). If you go with a trustworthy group (I go with a core of 5 + any one person) it is not tough at all. The thing that hurts most is if you get a string of resists on either a roamer or an odd pull due to the glorious pathing in there (sucks huge ~ and stuff gets stuck in the doorways and warps to you).
<br />

<br />
Well worth it, exp is decent, mobs mitigate like mad, I constantly see strings of single digit hits (1700+ attack) with crits hitting 35. It can be sad to see that kind of melee output. 
<br />

<br />
Odd thing about doing damage there that was reported by the ranger that has been going as our 6th. He will get a crit message that is for xxxx and what he sees below that is the non-melee damage message reporting the damage about 20% lower then the crit message. Happens all the time to him.
<br />

<br />
Insanely rare may be an understatement on its drop rate. We will see, I am thinking we will travel back to where they dropped and see if it had to do with location. If it proves true I will let you know Steppy.</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
